User Stories [Software developer using GroundUpDB]:-
[Who] As a software developer using GroundUpDB [What] I'd like to #include files as I do with other projects [Value] To make learning how to use GroundUpDB in C++ easier
[Who] As a software developer using GroundUpDB [What] I need to scope my imports to namespaces [Value] In order to avoid collisions in class and type names
[Who] As a software developer using GroundUpDB [What] I want to use an updated DB library without recompiling [Value] To minimise disruption to my application's users

DBMS Server Proxy Classes
- 'Client API' is viewed as 'external' and thus requires protection - Functional logic in public methods here

DBMS Server Implementation Classes
- Member variables here - Private methods here - Low level implementation choices here

Other stores will be part of the Embedded Database Impl in future
- E.g. Document, Columnar, Graph/Triple, search index and so on
This allows for a 'Remote Cluster Database' variant to be created in future.
Default implementation is file system based for now
User application only has knowledge of these classes
Server side extensions only have knowledge of these classes
Server side implementations hidden in these classes
